<img loading="lazy" class="aligncenter wp-image-1816628 lazyload lazyload" src="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/99C75B08-9EA9-4B80-9E81-E8AE497BC30A-835x1024-1-488x598.jpeg" alt="" width="1280" height="1570" /> Nigerian striker Peter Olayinka and his wife Yetunde Barnabas have welcomed their first baby. In a grandiose wedding, Olayinka, 26, married his wife back in June 2021. The couple have been married for a year and now have an addition to the family. Peter Olayinka and his wife Yetunde Barnabas shared a joint post on their respective official Instagram accounts announcing the birth of their child. In the Czech First League, Olayinka plays for Slavia Prague. He is married to Yetunde Barnabas, a well-known Nollywood actress. A statement was included with the newborn pictures in the joint Instagram post that was published on July 27, 2022. The message reads, “We have seen the Glory of GOD in our lives and We are saying thank You to the Most High for making us a parent to the most beautiful one GEMMA OLAYINKA 26/07/22 our bundle of happiness is here.” Olayinka and his wife posed for pictures with the newborn in the hospital. The infant was born in Prague, Czech Republic, where Olayinka performs professionally, according to the birth certificate. Super Falcons star Asisat Oshoala and Super Eagles players Paul Onuachu and Oghenekaro Etebo expressed their congratulations to the Olayinka family in the comments section. 